{"type":"assistant","message":{"type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"おつかれさまでした (おつかれさまでした — good work)! ✅\n\n**Summary of what was implemented:**\n\n- **`src/api/cache.rs`** — Generic `ResponseCache<V>` with TTL-based expiry. Supports `get` (fresh only), `get_stale` (ignores TTL for background-refresh patterns), `insert`, `invalidate`, `clear`, and `is_fresh`. Includes 13 unit tests covering expiry, staleness, invalidation, and TTL refresh.\n\n- **`src/app.rs`** — Added `cache: ResponseCache<Vec<Issue>>` field (5-minute TTL). New `load_issues()` serves from cache when fresh, otherwise fetches from API and populates the cache. `refresh()` (triggered by `r` keybinding) invalidates cache and force-fetches. Added 5 async integration tests for cache behavior.\n\n- **`src/main.rs`** — Initial issue load now uses `app.load_issues().await` which populates the cache for instant subsequent navigation."}],"stop_reason":"end_turn","usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":503,"cache_read_input_tokens":91298,"output_tokens":256,"max_tokens":168000,"service_tier":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"T-019cff7b-8cf5-735f-8f96-29fad7847eeb"}
